<owl:Class rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#Friendship">
  <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">A relationship between two players indicating they are friends.</rdfs:comment>
  <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Friendship</rdfs:label>
  <vaem:rationale>[Ontology Generation Agent] Created class Friendship: Required to model the friend relationship (CQ02, CQ03, CQ05, CQ07). It's a reified relationship to allow for potential attributes.
    [Logical Consistency Agent] Created class Friendship: Required to model the friend relationship (CQ02, CQ03, CQ05, CQ07). It's a reified relationship to allow for potential attributes.
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Created class Friendship: Required to model the friend relationship (CQ02, CQ03, CQ05, CQ07). It's a reified relationship to allow for potential attributes.: Initial creation based on competency questions
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Created class Friendship: Required to model the friend relationship (CQ02, CQ03, CQ05, CQ07). It's a reified relationship to allow for potential attributes.: Consistency check
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Added connections to Player class via hasFriendship and friendshipWith properties: Fix isolated class pitfall by connecting Friendship to Player</vaem:rationale>
  <dc:source>(competency_question) CQ02: Who are the friends of the player?
    (competency_question) CQ03: Who are the friends that play other games as well with this player?
    (competency_question) CQ05: What are the achievements of my friends?
    (competency_question) CQ07: What are the achievements your friend has received?
    (pitfall) Ontology elements (classes, object properties and datatype properties) are created isolated, with no relation to the rest of the ontology.</dc:source>
</owl:Class>

