<owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#hasFriend">
  <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Links a player to another player who is their friend.</rdfs:comment>
  <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">has friend</rdfs:label>
  <vaem:rationale>[Ontology Generation Agent] Created object property hasFriend: Required by CQ02, CQ03, CQ05, CQ07
    [Logical Consistency Agent] Created object property hasFriend: Required by CQ02, CQ03, CQ05, CQ07
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Created object property hasFriend: Required by CQ02, CQ03, CQ05, CQ07: Initial creation based on competency questions
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Created object property hasFriend: Required by CQ02, CQ03, CQ05, CQ07: Consistency check
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Added inverse property isFriendOf: Fix missing inverse relationship pitfall</vaem:rationale>
  <dc:source>(competency_question) CQ02: Who are the friends of the player?
    (competency_question) CQ03: Who are the friends that play other games as well with this player?
    (competency_question) CQ05: What are the achievements of my friends?
    (competency_question) CQ07: What are the achievements your friend has received?
    (pitfall) This pitfall appears when any relationship (except for those that are defined as symmetric properties using owl:SymmetricProperty) does not have an inverse relationship (owl:inverseOf) defined within the ontology.</dc:source>
  <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#Player"/>
  <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#Player"/>
  <owl:inverseOf rdf:resource='http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#isFriendOf'/>
</owl:ObjectProperty>

<owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#isFriendOf">
  <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Links a player to another player who considers them a friend. Inverse of hasFriend.</rdfs:comment>
  <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">is friend of</rdfs:label>
  <vaem:rationale>[Pitfall Resolution Agent] Created inverse property for hasFriend: Fix missing inverse relationship pitfall</vaem:rationale>
  <dc:source>(pitfall) This pitfall appears when any relationship (except for those that are defined as symmetric properties using owl:SymmetricProperty) does not have an inverse relationship (owl:inverseOf) defined within the ontology.</dc:source>
  <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#Player"/>
  <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#Player"/>
  <owl:inverseOf rdf:resource='http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#hasFriend'/>
</owl:ObjectProperty>

<owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#playsGame">
  <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Links a player to a game they have played.</rdfs:comment>
